<br>
I certainly never thought I would learn anything about wine in the Blast Furnace.<br>
<br>
...and I still laugh at the fools who insist the grape color has nothing to do with the wine color...all grape juice is almost clear, the color of wine comes from contact of the juice with the skins. If that is not correct, I really want to hear where the color of wine comes from.<br>
<br>
And my favorite wines of all time (which is really stupid to say since wines vary so much*) has to be Joseph Drouhin's Beaune &quot;Clos des Mouches&quot; in either <!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.wineandco.com/uk/e-vintage/liv-uk/produit-1882.html" target="top">red</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--> or <!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.wineandco.com/uk/e-vintage/liv-uk/produit-1881.html" target="top">white</a><!--EZCODE LINK END-->.<br>
<br>
* and when anyone asks me recommend a wine, I tell them drink whatever tastes best to you! But thats why taste is so interesting, we each have our own.<br>
